# GW2 Event Tracker

Blish HUD module (`namespace`: `ghost.gw2eventtracker`). .NET Framework 4.7.2, x64, Blish HUD 1.3+.

## Layout

| Area | Path |
|---|---|
| Entry | `EventTrackerModule.cs` |
| Settings | `Services/ModuleSettings.cs` |
| Schedule engine | `Services/EventScheduleEngine.cs`, `EventScheduleLoader.cs`, `EventSchedulePatcher.cs` |
| GW2 API progress | `Services/AccountProgressService.cs`, `TrackableRewardsCatalog.cs` |
| Alerts | `Services/AlertService.cs` |
| Main UI | `UI/EventTrackerView.cs`, `DailyProgressView.cs`, `SettingsView.cs`, `NextUpOverlayWidget.cs`, `EventCardUiHelper.cs`, `DailyRewardCard.cs` |
| Schedule data | `ref/Data/events.json`, `ref/Data/trackable-rewards.json` (embedded + copied into `.bhm`) |
| Manifest | `manifest.json` (UTF-8, no BOM) |

Do not edit `Data/` — it is gitignored; canonical JSON lives under `ref/Data/`.

## Key behavior

- **Daily reset** = 00:00 UTC. `EventScheduleEngine.DailyReset` clears snoozes/alerts; `AccountProgressService.EnsureUtcDay` clears completion cache on every UTC day change (also checked during API refresh and the 5s schedule tick).
- **Remote schedule** loads giovazz89 `events.json`; `EventSchedulePatcher` fixes gaps (e.g. renamed Amnytas meta, Inner Nayos).
- **Trackable reward names** in `trackable-rewards.json` must match segment names (or use `alsoAppliesTo` aliases).
- **UI threading**: use `GameService.Overlay.QueueMainThreadUpdate` for UI updates from async/API callbacks.

## Scripts

- `deploy.ps1` — Debug build + local install + restart Blish
- `publish.ps1` — Release build to `dist/` (local only, gitignored)
